postcontent:
LNIB Beretta 87BB, .22LR with LNIB AWC Archangel Suppressor $1650 Shipped; NFA rules apply re suppressor shipment and sale. Offered only as package.

Like-new condition; only used once in 1989 when it was fired 24 times. Comes with original Beretta factory threaded barrel and thread protector, two 8-round mags, deluxe wooden grips, original hard case, brush and manual. Package includes AWC Archangel Suppressor with manual and tool for disassembly; 7/16" X 28 threads, 7" long, 1" diameter, weight 10oz; suppression 36db. 

In Sept 1988 a handgun collector in Port Arthur, Texas received a call from Sile Distributers in NYC. The sales agent at Sile said that the Israeli Mossad had ordered a suppressed Beretta 87BB with factory threaded barrel and AWC suppressor but had, at the last minute, canceled the order. Sile sold the package to the TX collector. Sometime during the next year the Texas guy was curious as to how quiet the suppressed gun might be so he fired 24 rounds with suppressor installed. He cleaned the gun and suppressor and put it into his safe where it remained until I bought it about two years ago. By the time I secured my tax stamp and took possession I had lost interest. I have not fired it. If you have any questions or would like additional photos please let me know.

title: For Sale/Trade:  H&K HK4 pistol .32 ACP
postcontent:
Selling a Heckler & Koch HK4 pistol in .32 ACP (or, as the Europeans that made the gun call it, the 7.65mm). Introduced in 1967, this was the first pistol ever introduced by H&K, and definitely unlike any of its later, far more popular offerings. It most closely resembles a Walther PP/PPK style pistol with a double action / single action trigger, seven round magazine, and slide mounted safety, as well as a recoil spring which coils around the barrel and a straight blowback cycling mechanism.

It differs from the PP style in that it uses a European style heel magazine release and its barrel is not integral to its frame, and in fact the primary selling point of this model was that it is able to fire .22, .25, .32, and .380 calibers needing only a quick change of its barrel and magazine. It was popularly sold as a set with all four of these barrels included, and these sets are extremely collectible and worth thousands. Sadly, this one only has one barrel, in .32, and it's not worth very much.

It is, however, quite well built as you'd expect of an H&K and in good used condition, with only minor scratches and blemishes marring its original finish. It comes with THREE factory .32 8-round magazines -- each one s $50 value if purchased from Numrich parts supplier. Does NOT come with the original box. I expect most of the interest, if any, to come from H&K collectors and completionists.

Will include this as a bonus to go with my other offering currently for sale for the right trade:
http://www.armslist.com/posts/4543993/birmingham-alabama-handguns-for-sale-trade--s-w-1006-10mm-auto

title: For Sale:  Nighthawk Custom T3 Carry
postcontent:
The Ultimate Concealed Carry Pistol: They designed this little pistol to allow users to pack the powerful 45acp in a small package, but due to its popularity we now offer it in 9mm. A 4.25" bushing barrel allows field strip anywhere, and keeps the weight down when compared to pistols of comparable size with tapered cone barrels. Already loaded with options, we find that most customers want it just the way it is.
When it comes time to choose your everyday carry gun there is a lot to consider. You need something that is reliable, accurate, and easy to wear all day. You need something that you can enjoy shooting a lot, because there is no substitute for practice. That's where the T3 comes in. We designed this pistol to be pleasing to the eye, but also to be a workhorse that can stand up to thousands and thousands of rounds.
The T3 has the best features for any gun its size. The frame is based on the Officer model, but for those with large hands, it features an extended magazine well that gives you the length you need to get all your fingers on the grip. The extension also serves another function. The hand-cut geometric angles really add to the looks as well. The slide is a 4.25" Commander length that affords a better sight radius.
Another consideration is weight. The T3 actually weighs one ounce lighter than most officer size 1911s. This makes the T3 the first choice for an all-day carry pistol.
Heinie Slant-Pro Straight Eights Night Sights are standard. The mainspring housing, as well as the rear of the slide, are horizontally serrated to match. This feature also helps prevent snags on silk lined jackets and coats that checkering often causes. The top of the slide is also serrated to reduce glare. A Nighthawk Custom© lightweight aluminum trigger that has been blacked-out using Cerakote™ breaks between 3.5 and 4 lbs with no creep. When you put all of these features in one package, you come up with the finest carry gun you can own. 
This gun has been wonderful to own but I now have a newer model and will no longer be needing this one. Anyone that knows 1911s knows that not only is this pistol a weapon but is also a handcrafted piece of art. Here's a chance to own a sidearm that would take you months and months to get from Nighthawk and would cost a damn sight more. MSRP is $3350 and I'm only asking $2700 obo. i have for sale this used LWRC M6A2 Short Stroke Gas Piston 5.56 NATO AR15 Carbine with a Nikon M-223 4-16x40 Sniper Scope.The M6 is designed and manufactured by Land Warfare Resources Corporation.
It is based on the M4 carbine, with which it shares 80% of its parts.
It features a proprietary short-stroke self-regulating gas piston system and bolt carrier/carrier key design, which prevents trapped gases from contacting the bolt carrier or receiver of the weapon, which reduces the heating and carbon fouling of the internals, simplifies field maintenance, and improves reliability.
All M6A2 Rifles Feature a Match Grade, cold rotary hammer forged barrel with a target crown.
The barrel is treated with NiCorr™ surface conversion technology that extends service life, enhances accuracy, and increases the effective range of the weapon.
The bolt carrier group and the barrel extension of the M6A2 rifle is coated with EXO’s patented nickel-boron surface conversion technology that provides a hard permanent lubrication to the moving parts.
This M6A2 has a low- profile gas block and there is no A-frame front sight to obscure the field of view of the optical device.
it also features a longer mid-length free float rail system with rail covers and a removable return-to-zero top so that any M4 MIL Std 1913 accessory can be mounted to the rail.
The rail has a monolithic profile so you can bridge devices from the receiver to the rail seamlessly and the longer rail also affords more 1913 “real estate” to mount your accessories.
This High-End Rig is Topped with a High-End Nikon M-223 4-16x40 Sniper Scope with BDC.
It also has MOE Magpul Stock and a Magpul MIAD Pistol Grip.

Right-handed shooters can comfortably reach the magazine release on the LCP with their thumb, while left-handed shooters have no problem using their trigger finger. The mag release pushes in easily, but not so easily that the magazine pops out unexpectedly. Unlike many small semi-automatic pistols that operate with a blowback action, the Ruger LCP operates on a locked-breech system, which mitigates recoil and does not necessitate the user to pull the slide back against an excessively heavy recoil spring during loading.
